{"lemma":"رَجُلَيْ","slug":"رَجُلَيْ","root":"ر.ج.ل","root_slug":"ر-ج-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ج-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَجُل","root":"رجل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":29},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":10,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":16},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14936","n14938"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to go on foot, to walk"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to comb (the hair)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to let down (the hair)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"man (adult male human)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"obsolete form of رَجُل (rajul)","tags":["alt-of","obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an extremity; a limb; a leg","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an extremity; a limb; a hind leg","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"swarm (especially, of locusts)","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"common purslane (Portulaca oleracea)","tags":["collective","countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"going on foot, pedestrian, walking","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَجِلَ (rajila) (form I)","tags":["countable","form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pedestrian, traveler on foot","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"neither lank nor crisp, neither scrawny nor shredded, neither svelte nor portly, well on foot due to not having excess mass","tags":["countable"],"examples":[{"text":"رَأَيْتُ مُوسَى وَإِذَا رَجُلٌ ضَرْبٌ رَجِلٌ، كَأَنَّهُ مِنْ رِجَالِ شَنُوءَةَ، وَرَأَيْتُ عِيسَى، فَإِذَا هُوَ رَجُلٌ رَبْعَةٌ أَحْمَرُ كَأَنَّمَا خَرَجَ مِنْ دِيمَاسٍ","english":"I saw Moses who was a man neither of a scrawny nor a shredded stature, as though he were of the Šanūʾa men, and I saw Jesus, cobby and red as though he had come out of a bathhouse."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"foal which is allowed to suck freely","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of رَاجِل (rājil)","tags":["countable","form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of رَجِل (rajil)","tags":["countable","form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Originally \"walker\", attested with the meaning \"footsoldier\" as Safaitic 𐪇𐪔𐪁 (rgl).\n\nFrom Proto-Semitic *rigl-."},"ipa":["/ra.d͡ʒi.la/","/rad͡ʒ.d͡ʒa.la/","/ra.d͡ʒul/","/rid͡ʒl/","/ra.d͡ʒil/","/rad͡ʒl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14936","headword_ar":"رجْلَي","root":"rjl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajolaAnu","text_ar":"رَجْلَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAjilN","text_ar":"رَاجِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"near the end of the paragraph. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Har~apN rajolay","text_ar":"حَرَّةٌ رَجْلَي"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajolaA='u","text_ar":"رَجْلَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stony tract such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Har~ap","text_ar":"حَرَّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is rough"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rugged"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which one goes on foot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"level, but abounding with stones:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rough and difficult, in which one cannot go except on foot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the latter signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"level, but abounding with stones, in which it is difficult to go along:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard and rough, which horses and camels cannot traverse, and none can but a man on foot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or that impedes the feet by its difficulty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajolay","text_ar":"رَجْلَي"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajolaAnu","text_ar":"رَجْلَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) [and app. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajiylN","text_ar":"رَجِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also.]"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","AHeyth"]},{"entry_id":"n14938","headword_ar":"رَجَلِيٌّ","root":"rjl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaliy~uwna","text_ar":"رَجَلِيُّونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which latter is applied, with the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain men who used to run"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAnuwA yaEoduwna","text_ar":"كَانُوا يَعْدُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", so in the O and K, but in the T"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yagozuwna","text_ar":"يَغْزُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is evidently a mistranscription], TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon their feet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rujayolaA='u","text_ar":"رُجَيْلَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in like manner with the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K, TA:) in the T, the sing. is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajoliy~N","text_ar":"رَجْلِيٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and said to be a rel. n. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ujolapu","text_ar":"الرُّجْلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which requires consideration: (TA:) they were Suleyk El-Makánib, (O, K, TA,) i. e. Ibn-Sulakeh, (TA,) and El-Munteshir Ibn-Wahb El-Báhilee, and Owfà Ibn-Matar ElMázinee. (O, K, TA. [All these were famous runners.])"}],"source_refs":["O","K","TA"]}]}}